      "writtenOn": "2021-02-22T16:44:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s not quite correct, the uniforms is always getUniformFloatCount long, we just differentiate between the predefined uniforms we prepend to every shader and the uniforms defined in the provided shader code.\n\nThis differentiation makes more sense once child shaders show up in a future CL, as all shaders will share the same set of predefined uniforms, but every child shader will possibly have a different set of local uniforms.",
      "parentUuid": "3b250f5d_6905a342",
